2026-04-25 01:46:25 [DEBUG] llm.engine: RESULT: answer='import json\nfrom typing import List, Optional\n\nclass Pipeline:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.data: Optional[List[int]] = None\n    \n    def load(self, query: str) -> \'Pipeline\':\n        """Simulates loading data based on a search query."""\n        # Simulate query-based filtering/loading\n        if query:\n            # Example: if query contains \'large\', start with larger numbers\n            base = [100, 200, 300] if \'large\' in query else [1, 2, 3]\n        else:\n            base = [1, 2, 3]\n        \n        self.data = base\n        print(f"Loaded {len(self.data)} items for query: \'{query}\'")\n        return self\n    \n    def search(self, query: str) -> List[int]:\n        """Searches/filter the loaded data based on a query."""\n        if not self.data:\n            raise ValueError("No data loaded. Call load() first.")\n        \n        results = []\n        for item in self.data:\n            # Simple search logic - can be customized\n            if query.lower() in str(item):\n                results.append(item)\n            elif not query:  # No filter means return all\n                results.append(item)\n        \n        print(f"Search \'{query}\' returned {len(results)} items")\n        return results\n    \n    def execute(self, query: Optional[str] = None) -> List[int]:\n        """Main pipeline execution."""\n        if query:\n            self.load(query)\n        else:\n            self.load("")\n        \n        # If a specific search query is provided\n        if query and len(query.strip()) > 0:\n            return self.search(query)\n        else:\n            return self.data or []\n\n# Example usage:\npipeline = Pipeline()\nresults = pipeline.execute(query="large")\nprint(f"Final results: {results}")'
